title: Scuffle breaks out at summit in Turkey after Russian delegate takes down Ukrainian flag
description: Fighting broke out at a summit in Turkey after a Russian delegate pulled down a Ukrainian flag.

title: Grenada expresses 'hope' of becoming republic on eve of coronation
description: Grenada is showing increasing interest in becoming a republic, with the country's prime minister hoping it will be under his leadership.

title: Six killed in Pakistan school shooting in possible retaliation for earlier teacher death
description: Six people, including four teachers and two other members of staff, have been killed in a shooting at a school in Pakistan.

title: Two killed after train crashes into track workers in Germany
description: Two people have been killed and several others have been treated for shock after a train crash near the western German city of Cologne.

title: Olympic wrestlers clash with police during #MeToo protest in Delhi
description: Police in Delhi were involved in scuffles with Indian Olympic wrestlers at a #MeToo protest in the Indian capital city.

title: Trump attacks rape accuser as 'fake woman' and says he will 'probably' attend trial
description: Former US president Donald Trump has described his civil rape trial as a "political attack", based on the "false accusations" of a "fake woman".

title: European Central Bank hikes interest rates again
description: The European Central Bank (ECB) has raised interest rates again to maintain its battle against inflation but eased the pace of increase.

title: War news for Russians hidden inside video game
description: Finland's largest daily newspaper is fighting back against Russia's media restrictions by hiding news about the war in Ukraine in a secret room within a video game.

title: Seven bodies found in search for missing teenagers were shot in 'murder-suicide'
description: An Oklahoma sex offender who was freed from prison early shot dead his wife, her three children and their two friends in the head before killing himself, authorities have confirmed.

title: King salmon fishing could be shut down in Southeast Alaska
description: The future of commercial king salmon trolling in Southeast Alaska has been thrown into doubt after a court ruled on the threat it poses to the protected fish and endangered killer whales that eat them.

title: Churches and homes attacked and set ablaze in India violence
description: Dozens of churches and homes have been attacked, vandalised and set ablaze after violence erupted in India.

title: Palestinian gunmen who shot dead British-Israeli family are killed
description: Two Palestinian gunmen who shot dead a British-Israeli mother and her two daughters last month have been killed, Israel's domestic security service said.

title: Shell hands £4.7bn to shareholders as quarterly profits beat forecasts
description: Shell has revealed it is handing a further $6bn (£4.7bn) to shareholders after its latest quarterly profits beat its own forecasts.

title: Ukraine shoots down more than a dozen Russian-launched drones
description: Ukraine has said it has shot down more than a dozen Russian-launched drones in the early hours of Thursday morning.

title: At least 129 dead due to torrential rainfall in Rwanda
description: At least 129 people have been killed after torrential rain caused flooding in Rwanda.
